{
  "files": [
    {"repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express", "path": "lib/request.js"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express", "path": "test/req.host.js"},
    {"repo": "sg-evals/expressjs-express", "path": "History.md"}
  ],
  "text": "The deprecated req.host property is referenced in three files within the sg-evals/expressjs-express repository. The property was deprecated in Express 4.3.0 in favor of req.hostname. In lib/request.js (lines 452-456), the deprecated req.host property is formally defined using defineGetter with an explicit deprecation message: 'req.host: Use req.hostname instead'. The definition returns this.hostname, establishing the replacement relationship. In test/req.host.js, comprehensive tests verify the deprecated req.host property's behavior across multiple scenarios including basic host retrieval, port stripping, IPv6 handling, and trust proxy configurations. In History.md, the changelog documents the deprecation context at line 1286 ('deprecate req.host -- use req.hostname instead'), explains the replacement at line 1284 ('add req.hostname -- correct name for what req.host returns'), and records historical fixes to the deprecated property at lines 799 and 1436. These three files constitute the complete set of source files in the Express.js repository that specifically reference the deprecated req.host property."
}

